#UnisonMedHat #veinercentre We were honored to have MLA Justin Wright visit Unison at Veiner Centre today! We appreciate Justin and his team for taking the time to stop by and get a firsthand look at the work we're doing to support seniors in our community. 

During his visit, we had the opportunity to showcase the various programs and services we offer, all aimed at enhancing the lives of Medicine Hat seniors. From Elder Abuse Case Management and Meals on Wheels to our NEW Transportation Service, Seniors Supports and Food Security, we're committed to ensuring that our senior residents thrive in every way possible. 🌼 #MedHat

#Repost @unison50plus with @use.repost
・・・
#UnisonCalgary A few weeks ago we had Dana Mackie, Assistant Deputy Minister for Seniors and Angella Gauthier (Director, Senior Strategy and Program support – she oversees the Elder Abuse portfolio) came by for a tour! 

Dana’s team was the team responsible for working with us to create a proposal to the Minister which more than doubled the province’s annual financial commitment to the Shelter. They came to see what their commitment had resulted in. They have been impressed with the work our team is doing in the Elder Abuse area and our team’s leadership in the sector. Angella has been the creator of the new provincial elder abuse response plan. A part of the purpose for their visit was to ask us to be involved in a larger way with the execution of the provincial plan. 

#olderadults #elderabuseshelter #elderabuseawareness

#UnisonMedHat Help us support seniors who are struggling with food insecurity, especially during this holiday season! Visit UnisonAlberta.com/MedHat-Donate to give a hand up to seniors. 

Part of our mission at Unison is to help low-income seniors who have difficulties ensuring they have access to food. 

Through our Thrive Food Security Program, we are able to help with initiatives such as Meals on Wheels, Wellness Market and recently we've launched our Community Kitchen. 

Our Meals on Wheels alone received 147 applications from January 1st to October 31st of 2023. We were able serve over 300 seniors, 58 of those being subsidized. So far this year, our Wellness Market has also helped rescue and distribute over 4 tonne of food to seniors in Medicine Hat! And lastly, our Community Kitchen not only helps with those who are low-income, it also provides a space for social interaction, reducing isolation and fostering a sense of community. 

Help Unison continue to offer this support to seniors in need. Visit UnisonAlberta.com/MedHat-Donate to give seniors a hand up this holiday season!

#UnisonCalgary It's no secret that food banks are busier than ever, and the recent Food Banks Canada survey tells us that Calgary is leading the way in food insecurity. Food prices have soared to astronomical heights, the highest in 41 years, and about 1 in 4 Calgarians are having a tough time making ends meet when it comes to putting food on the table. 

You can make a real difference this winter. Your donation, big or small, can help us fight food insecurity and ensure that vulnerable adults don't have to struggle for a simple meal. Even a modest contribution can mean a warm dinner on someone's table during these cold winter nights. 

Visit UnisonAlberta.com/Calgary-Donate/ to help 

 
#HelpfortheHolidays #OlderAdults #FoodInsecurity #DonateNow

#UnisonCalgary Here at Unison, we're doing our part to tackle the issue of food insecurity head-on. Our Thrive Department has been hard at work, running bi-weekly Free Food Markets (Tuesdays and Fridays), Free Food Basket delivery on Wednesdays, and our Community Food Pantry. We're here to lend a hand and a meal to those who need it most. 

But here's the thing – the demand is growing, and the line at our Food Market gets longer every week. This holiday season, we want to ensure that every senior at Unison's Kerby Centre has enough food to eat. Because let's face it, there's nothing more important than having a meal on your plate, especially for those who cannot afford it. 

Your donation, big or small, can help us fight food insecurity and ensure that vulnerable adults don't have to struggle for a simple meal. Even a modest contribution can mean a warm dinner on someone's table during these cold winter nights. 

Visit UnisonAlberta.com/Calgary-Donate/ to help
